name: Growing Up Gracefully
overview: Sisters Hannah & Eliza Reilly are two misguided twentysomethings, who after rediscovering the 1950's teen-advice book 'Growing Up Gracefully', ask themselves, as young women in 2017, how do we learn to grow up?

episodes.name: Looking Your Best
episodes.overview: In this episode, sisters Hannah and Eliza Reilly learn how to look their best from the 'Queen' of etiquette and beauty - June Dally Watkins. Hannah learns about appropriate hem length, while Eliza fills her face with Botox.

episodes.name: Courtship
episodes.overview: In the good old days dating was simple. Hannah follows the old world advice from books & tests whether playing dumb on a date actually works, while Eliza creates a 'unique' experience with an adrenalin inducing surprise.

episodes.name: Hosting A Party
episodes.overview: Hannah & Eliza find out how to make friends & be popular. They follow old & new advice on making conversation, planning a party & being the perfect hostess. Eliza uses the internet to become a cool girl & find her squad.

episodes.overview: How should young ladies navigate the workforce? Eliza goes big to get an employer's attention & tests being a 'bitch' to get ahead. Hannah tests the old method of being a nurturing mother to the boys at work.
